snippet: Prime Minister David Cameron is heading for Amsterdam on Friday to set out his vision of a sharply whittled-down role for Britain in 21st-century Europe.
abstract: British Prime Min David Cameron is heading to Amsterdam to set out his vision of sharply whittled-down role for Britain in affairs of 21st-century Europe.

byline.contributor: Alan Cowell contributed reporting from Paris, and Stephen Castle from London.

lead_paragraph: Prime Minister David Cameron is heading for Amsterdam on Friday to set out his vision of a sharply whittled-down role for Britain in 21st-century Europe.

headline.seo: Cameron to Outline a Recast European Role for Britain
headline.main: Prime Minister Ready to Stake Britain’s European Role on a Referendum
